cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about a framework for neural networks and deep learning.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the framework leverages data-based parallelism on shared- or distributed-memory machines.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses optimization algorithms and performance evaluation.
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses Fortran derived types and whole-array arithmetic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper describes the interface for constructing feed-forward neural networks.
